Risk Management Plan
Carl Buddig and Company

I. Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Carl Buddig and Company (Carl Buddig) facility located at 50 West Taft Drive in South Holland, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials.  This 5-year resubmission for the Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases.  The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including:
- Carl Buddig policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
- Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
- Hazard Assessment;
- Prevention Program;
- Five-Year Accident History;
- Emergency Response Plan;
- Emergency Communications;
- Spill Reporting/Environmental Release Procedures
- Planned changes to improve safety; and
- Management Program

II. Carl Buddig Policies to Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Carl Buddig; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities.  Carl Buddig is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment.  It is Carl Buddig's policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

